reviews.author: Francisco García Villavicencio
reviews.text: An art gallery in a prime area of ​​Lima, overlooking one of the few remaining huacas in the city. The exhibitions are well-curated for the space, sober and aesthetically balanced. They represent prominent Peruvian artists who work with languages ​​ranging from the culture generated in the country to a connection with the world. If you're nearby, don't miss this spot in Lima, where you can breathe the past, present, and future.
